Completed the task_3 via Windows Power Shell.

Create test.txt file using  "echo text content > test.txt" command
Used the following commands:
Get-Content -path test.txt command for checking the content or the replacement of the words within the file
Get-Content -path test.txt -Raw
(Get-Content -path test.txt -Raw) -replace 'test','DONE
(Get-Content -path test.txt -Raw) -replace 'test','DONE' | Set-Content -Path test.txt' for replacing the keyword

Used "Move-Item -Path test.txt -Destination test.replace.txt" command to move a file to another one and renamed it:
 move test.txt file to another remnamed one - test.replace.txt

